; Test that --download does not fetch duplicate quotes for the same commodity
; when it appears across multiple postings (issue #996).
;
; Prior to the fix, find_price() called with a historical moment (midnight)
; could not see a price already downloaded with a later time component on the
; same date.  This caused check_for_updated_price() to re-download on every
; posting that referenced the commodity.  The fix adds last_quote tracking to
; commodity_t::base_t so that a successful download within the leeway window
; suppresses subsequent download attempts for that commodity.

2013/10/21 Buy Stock A
    Assets:Brokerage        10 AAPL
    Assets:Checking        $-1000.00

2013/10/21 Buy More Stock A
    Assets:Brokerage        5 AAPL
    Assets:Checking        $-500.00

2013/10/21 Buy Stock B
    Assets:Brokerage        2 GOOG
    Assets:Checking        $-2000.00

test bal --market --download --getquote $sourcepath/test/scripts/mock-getquote.sh -> 0
           $-1050.00  Assets
            $2450.00    Brokerage
           $-3500.00    Checking
--------------------
           $-1050.00
end test
